reviewText: Yes! It has come to this: A [seperate] BONUS FEATURES release. The Assylum has sucked ME into their franchise, er, uh... hook; line; and sinker! At 77-minutes---with a Diet Coke---I can, now, hear about inappropriate humour involving shark attacks... something that, normally, wouldn't raise a grin, but would, a grimace. Starts out with NINE up-front preview-trailers; ends with a sneak-peek of Sharknado 3: Oh hell no! Not Academy/Emmy Award winning stuff, but like Supernatural; The Walking Dead;Ancient Aliens; and, Mythbusters, it IS just a subject that's more popular than important matters such as VOTING. I may not believe in The President... or a-c-t-u-a-l ancient aliens, but, I believe in rubber sharks that KILL! Put ME in "The Assylum"!

Much of it was mildly amusing, but, on the whole, this entire production belongs on a Sharknado 3 Extras package. $15 for this?: No Effing way!

They're charging us for extra features now!!!

R-I-P  O-F-F!!!

While I like variety in the content of my Instant Video library, my ENTIRE FAMILY agrees that the Sharknado series is CRAP!!!  If it were possible to still return these movies, we would.  We are completely dissatisfied with these purchases.
